comments.body:
@ericwj: 

This is a general issue: The `-ErrorAction` common parameter applies to _nonterminating_ errors only; it has no effect on _statement-terminating_ errors, which are what `Invoke-WebRequest` now reports in the situations discussed.

Note that the `$ErrorActionPreference` _preference variable_ still applies, however - see [this doc issue](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell-Docs/issues/1583).

For those looking for a workaround:

```powershell
try {
    Invoke-WebRequest -Method HEAD http://cnn.com -MaximumRedirection 0 -ErrorAction Stop
} catch {
    $Location = $_Exception.Response.Headers.Location
}
```
